le> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukrugkopf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krugkopf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 10:10:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1986.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The reasons there are happy rogues?</span><hr size=1> Excepting what I've seen on the Vault boards, it seems to me that most assassins out there are happier overall about their class than before.  I know that I am.  But why is this?  It isn't like we've been helped much in the PvE department, where we most needed the tweaking.  The last change to the PvE department that I can recall is the elimination of the weapon spec cap, and the insertion of Evade VII.  I remember everyone ridiculing about how pathetic the change was.  I was part of that crowd.<br><br>Nowadays, few assassins complain.  Is it because those of us who did bother to &quot;waste&quot; points in weapon specialization are the only ones who've stayed?  Is it because we might have an eternity of PvE frustration, but in the RvR frontier we are the avatars of power?<br><br>I'm curious, because I know that I still play my assassin.  I'm a 2/3 weapon specced shadowblade and happy with it, and the stories I hear about assassins on the Frontier keep me motivated to play.<br><br>Or am I misguided in my assessment of popular Assassin (only those who currently play one) opinion? <p><i>"People will believe any lie you give them; whether it is because they wish it to be true, or fear it to be true." -<b>Wizard's First Rule</i></b><Br><Br><b>Mundus Vult Decipi</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukosmaul.showPublicProfile?l