n Krug and I have wondered the same thing - I am always picking apart people's &quot;Rogue's suck&quot; posts, but I wouldn't call myself a fanboi.  I decided the answer is one of your suggestions - we are great in RvR.<br><br>Most of my guild has to shout for a group to go RvR - when I feel like it, I just go.  If any of my guild is in emain when I go, they are happy to have me join the group.  We are still weak in PvE - I still lfg for over an hour many times to get one.  But Mythic stated (Scott Jennings) that they want this class hard to play.  At first I thought they meant the stalking and escaping part, and I think that's part of it, but I also think they have no desire to make us strong in PvE as well as RvR.  It's one of the balancing parts of our class.<br><br>Rogues are hard to level.  They are frustrating to play in PvE.  For this reason a lot of people don't like the class, and I don't blame them.  But we are powerful in RvR with a host of unique abilities, and that's why I like my rogue.  Whenever I spend 2 or 3 hours lfg and never get a good one, I head to emain.  By the end of the night I forget about deleting my rogue. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utaleria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taleria</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/controlcenter/image/button_help.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 8:51:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1986.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hierophant.homestead.com/files/monkey.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why my SB is happy</span><hr size=1> Keep that up and all the people in emain will be purple to you. <p><center>Taleria Reznor<BR>60 Warlock<BR><im