bring that to close to level.<br><br><br>1) detect hidden fixed (the change on test server isn't real great)<br>2) perforate artery from any facing<br>3) poison damage scaling <br>4) lower endurance costs on garrote significantly<br><br><br>End of list.<br><br>That is all I want and what I will be fighting for.<br><br> <p><B><font color="#660033">Bile Silhouette</B><BR>Smurf of Death<br>-LEGENDS-<br>Pendragon<br><br><i>Half the world is composed of idiots, the other half of people clever enough to take indecent advantage of them.</i><br><br><b>BILE WAZ HERE!</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ebullition>Ebullition</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 5:02:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1986.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why my SB is happy</span><hr size=1> In my opinion the assassin needs PvM help, especially pre-level 40.  After level 40 I do think the class improves.<br><br>However, no matter how bad it gets I will ONLY play an assassin, and right now what options do I have?  Go back to UO, go back to EQ, wait for the next on-line roll playing game?<br><br>Good or bad, in my opinion DAOC is the best available at the moment.  So here I am.<br><br>Also, sometimes great things happen that make it all worth it.<br><br>The other night I was wandering the frontier, I am level 47.  I saw a yellow con Paladin.  I start running behind him unstealthed.  He knows I am there, but every time I close I hide.  He runs, I run. He stops, I stealth.<br><br>Finally he decides that he can kill me.  He turns to face me, but I hide and keep moving towards him and to the side as much as possible.  I get behind him.<br><br>He bows to where he last saw me, right as he comes up from his bow I hit him with Backstab and the Enervating poison.  After the stun wears off he turns to face me and to fight.  He gets a block in and I get an evade in, and we duke it out, sword to sword.<br><br>In the end he dies.  I sit down next to his corpse with a little less than half my hit points left and I rest.<br><br>That was a great moment.<br><br>Another great moment happened a few weeks ago when I saw a yellow con enemy rogue near one of our frontier keeps.  I get behind him.  I stalk him up the hill towards the door.  There are about 10 or 15 of my realm mates standing there.  I hit Backstab and get a bonus crit of 350 damage, so I do a total of about 700 damage to this yellow con rogue.  He dies in one hit, I remain hidden, and everyone turns to look at his corpse.  I unstealth, bow to the crowd, stealth, and move on.  That was priceless.<br><br>These little moments of sucess make all the struggles of leveling worth it.  <br><br>Do I think the melee rogue needs help?  Hell yes!!  Do I think Mythic sucks for lying to us about disguise and our skills?  Hell yes!!<br><br>But I keep on keeping on.  And I have to say I highly agree with one of the earlier posters that basically said it is best to avoid stress.  That is a HUGE issue for me.  I am trying to be happy and not let the bad things get me down too much.  Mythic doesn't care if I get angry, they don't respond when I complain, and as far as I can tell they don't give a rat's ass about the melee rogue community, but getting angry about all of that doesn't hurt them... it hurts me.<br><br>Have fun.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaxterixenobelix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Axterix EnObelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 5:05:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1986.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why my SB is happy</span><hr size=1> I think a lot of it has to do with information being out there.<br><br>People now know better what to spec in early.  That makes PvE more enjoyable.  Additionally, people playing the assassin classes know they are going to have it rough with levelling.  For the most part, they've accepted this fact and while they may not be happy with it, they aren't going to let it make them unhappy with the class.<br><br>A lot of the big whiners have left, that helps as well.  Many of the calmer heads remain and I think that most of us have some faith that Mythic will continue to tweak the classes.<br><br>In the meantime, we know we rock in RvR.<br><br>At least I do<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukendaile.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kendaile</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 6:44:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1986.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why my SB is happy</span><hr size=1> Maiya Hit it..  but you forgot one thing..<br><br>3.  Most of the loudest complainers have already quit and left.<br><br>... However, for the most part, those that were complaining were trying to get something done.. (which was promptly ignored by the powers that be, but that's beside the point) <p><I>Do I get to be the Avatar of Mischief yet?</I><br>"Float like a butterfly, sting like a poison-tipped curved dagger in the breadbasket... er.. wait a sec.."<br>Commander Kendaile MaelLeidh, Officer of the Grey Hand [Hibernia, Percival]<br><B>"www.greyhand.com"</B><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubalorgafdan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balor Gafdan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 7:52:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1986.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: More like Content</span><hr size=1> I for the most part am happy?  Not happy per se, but content.  I had the advantage of the previous Nighthshades who came before me.  I used their wisdom to build my own powers.   Yes, I varied from the &quot;normal&quot; template and pumped skills into stealth early, but I also kept my weapon skill 1/2 spec'd and let envenom fall to the wayside, but have started to catch it up now.  So I'm almost Full Stealth, Full Critical Strike, 1/2 Piercing, 1/2 Envenom<br><br>My guild refers to me as, &quot;Ginsu Knife (or sometimes Food Processor )  who can't take a Hit&quot;<br>The key point to that is GUILD.  Without a guild I'd still be 10 levels back around 25.  With my guild I can find groups.  No problem.  I appreciate them for this and repay them with whatever kindness and gratitude I can.  This is part of being in a top notch guild.. The Black Watch-Guinivere.<br><br>I would really like to see our &quot;spellcasting&quot; ability built upon and perhaps enhanced to follow the same line that the rangers do.<br><br>RvR is great.  Love it.. makes it hard for me to want to level.<br><br>PvM is slightly better than bad.  I have the ability to solo blues and the very RARE yellow with downtime, but everyone knows that the higher your level, groups become more and more beneficial.<br><br>To answer the original question..  <br><br>Happy? No.<br>Content at the moment? Yes. <p><p><p style="text-align: left; font-size: 80%; font-family: Verdana">Balor Gafdan Nightshade of Guinivere<br><i>What life brings, is it ours to take?.<br>Adreneline feeds my soul, feeds my need<br>Kiss the blades edge I hold for thee.  Silence....</i></p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showMessage?topicID=2042.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showMessage?topicID=2055.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1986.topic&index=17><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=1986.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.threadControl?topicID=1986.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1986.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1986.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=f